===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive|legal}} To [[borrow]] against a property, to obtain a [[loan]] for another purpose by giving away the right of seizure to the lender over a fixed property such as a house or piece of land; to pledge a property in order to get a loan.
#: {{ux|en|to '''mortgage''' a property, an estate, or a shop}}
#: {{ux|en|We '''mortgaged''' our house in order to start a company.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|figurative}} To pledge and make liable; to make subject to obligation; to achieve an immediate result by paying for it in the long term.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1982|author=Verne Moberg|title=The Truth and Work of [[w:Victoria Benedictsson|Victoria Benedictsson]]|page=72|passage=She '''mortgaged''' her future for the pleasures of the relationship with the sculptor, a relationship she knew would be short.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2001|author=Antony Rowland|title=[[w:Tony Harrison|Tony Harrison]] and the Holocaust|page=193|passage=Like a latter-day [[w:Faustus|Faustus]] who has '''mortgaged''' his soul to the pursuit of his art, Harrison now desperately craves the paternal love from which his learning has estranged him.}}

